<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--PostOfficeOusted     05-17 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Post Office Ousted,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Front Porch Post Office Closes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARLIN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The post office is being kicked off Ada
Meikrantz' front porch.
   And it could take two years to find and approve a new post
office for the tiny Traverse County community, said Carol Putnam,
the U.S. Postal Service's discontinuance coordinator in Washington,
D.C.
   ``You can't do it overnight,'' Putnam said.
   Postmaster Naomi Hayward, whois being transferred to Cedar, said
she'll miss distributing mail to Karlin's 100 residents.
   ``It's like my family,'' she said. ``We know when somebody's
sick and when they need help.''
   The Karlin post office, which has 80 mail boxes, lost its lease
when Meikrantz sold her home.
   Hayward learned of the decision to close last week.
   By mail.
   She received a letter Thursday from Brandon Burton, acting
director of field operations for the Postal Service's Grand Rapids
division.
