<NOTE>No. 3 NASA Official Chosen</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Samuel W. Keller, a veteran NASA official, has
been named to the No. 3 job in the space agency.
   His appointment as associate deputy administrator was one of the
first actions by the acting head of NASA, Richard Truly, who
assumed the job Monday.
   ``I will be filling other top jobs as quickly as I can,'' said
Truly, whose own confirmation hearings are to begin soon. ``I
intend to do all that I can to ensure that NASA continues to
maintain and attract a team dedicated to excellence.''
   Keller, deputy associate administrator for space science and
applications since December 1977, succeeds Dr. Noel W. Hinners, one
of several NASA officials who resigned recently because of new
post-employment laws and the failure of a pay raise to pass
Congress.
   President Bush nominated J.R. Thompson, head of the Marshall
Space Flight Center, for the deputy administrator's position, also
left vacant by a recent resignation. That nomination also is
pending confirmation.
