<HEAD>Six Killed in Northern Bulgaria Storm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hailstorm in northern Bulgaria killed
six people, washed out crops and damaged buildings, the state news
agency said Wednesday.
   The storm Tuesday caused losses estimated at $15 million in the
region, according to the news agency BTA.
   In the Danube River city of Ruse, the storm disrupted traffic
and flooded streets, the agency said. The main rail station, a soft
drink factory, a theater under construction and scores of homes
were among the buildings damaged, the agency said.
   The storm also knocked out power in six villages near Svishtov
and Razgrad and destroyed tens of thousands of acres of crops and
vineyards, it said.
