<HEAD>Somalia Jet Skids Off Runway During Takeoff; 1 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Somalia Airlines jetliner skidded off
the runway during takeoff Wednesday from Nairobi, but only one
minor injury was reported, police said.
   The Boeing 707, carrying 69 people on a flight to Somalia's
capital of Mogadishu, apparently lost power and skidded in the mud
about 1,000 feet beyond the runway, according to a police officer
who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   ``One passenger was treated for bruises at the airport clinic
and then released,'' he said. ``It could have been worse had it not
been for the rain earlier in the day that made the ground soggy. A
minor fire started at the left side undercarriage, but it was
immediately extinguished.''
   There had been a downpour earlier in the day, although it wasn't
raining at the time of the accident.
