quantum physics and the Big Bang theory _ and did it with a bit of
humor.
   Hawking has amyotropic lateral sclerosis, a degenerative
condition known as Lou Gehrig's disease, and spoke Tuesday through
a computerized speech synthesizer that he manipulates with tiny
movements of his crippled hands.
   ``It gives me a voice that sounds almost human except it has no
dialect,'' said Hawking, author of the bestseller ``A Brief History
of Time.'' ``It gives me an accent that has been variously
described as American, Scandinavian or Irish.''
