<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Drugs,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>Drug Smugglers Hanged In Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran on Wednesday hanged 13 people
convicted of drug trafficking, Tehran radio reported.
   The men smuggled 1,250 pounds of narcotics into Tehran,
according to the broadcast, which was monitored in Nicosia. Some
also were convicted on charges of smuggling arms, illegal
possession of weapons and illegal entry into the country, the radio
said.
   Wednesday's hangings raised to 605 the number of drug
traffickers executed since a new anti-narcotics law went into
effect in January. The law mandates the death penalty for anyone
caught with even small quantities of drugs.
