<FILEID>AP-NR-05-17-89 2208EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w AM-US-NorthKorea     05-17 0212</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US-North Korea,210</SECOND>
<HEAD>US, North Korean Diplomats Meet in Beijing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Diplomater comment.
   The U.S.-Korean talk took place during the historic
fence-mending visit to Beijing of President Mikhail Gorbachev of
the Soviet Union, the country regarded as a main supporter of North
Korea.
   North Korea has consistently demanded withdrawal of the more
than 40,000-member U.S. military force in South Korea as a
precondition to normalizing relations and unifying North and South
Korea.
   The United States describes its military presence as a deterrent
to North Korean aggression or renewal of fighting in the Korean
War. Although that war was waged from 1950 to 1953, it never
officially ended and technically has remained in a state of
armistice.
