<FIRST>r i AM-Haiti     05-17 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Haiti,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nine Injured In Blast Near Palace</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE, Haiti (AP) _ An explosion erupted as a crowd
gathered on a plaza for holiday celebrations, injuring nine people,
independent Radio Haiti Inter said Wednesday.
   Police made no statement on the cause of the explosion Tuesday
night and could not be reached for comment Wednesday.
   Most of the victims suffered minor injuries, but a 25-year-old
woman underwent surgery and remained in serious condition, the
radio station said.
   The explosion occurred on the central Champ de Mars Plaza, near
the National Palace. The injured were taken to the State University
Hospital a few blocks from the scene.
   The crowd had gathered at the Occide Jeanty bandstand in the
plaza for official pre-Flag Day festivities featuring groups of
young singers and artists. Radio Haiti Inter said the explosion
occurred near the crowd, but did not elaborate.
   Flag Day, scheduled to take place Thursday, is a national
holiday in Haiti and commemorates the creation of Haiti's red and
blue flag in 1803, a year before the Caribbean nation won its war
of independence from France.
</TEXT>
