<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Hewlett-Packard     05-17 0204</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Hewlett-Packard,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hewlett-Packard Reports Flat Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALO ALTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hewlett-Packard Co. on Wednesday
reported flat second-quarter earnings in spite of a 15 percent
increase in revenue.
   Net earnings totaled $203 million, or 86 cents a share, in the
period ended April 30, compared with net earnings of $202 million,
or 82 cents a share, in the second quarter of last year. Net
revenue reached $2.86 billion, compared with $2.50 billion in the
year-ago period.
   For the first six months of its fiscal year, the maker of
computers and scientific instruments said its earnings rose 4
percent to $396 million, or $1.69 a share, from $381 million, or
$1.53 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 18 percent to $5.52
billion from $4.69 billion.
   Hewlett-Packard warned on Monday that second-quarter earnings
would be lower than expected.
   The company predicted in Monday's announcement that net earnings
would be 85 cents to 90 cents per share while the average Wall
Street estimate had been $1. That announcement caused a sharp drop
in its stock.
   ``We experienced strong orders for most product lines throughout
the second quarter, yet our net revenues and profits did not meet
expectations,'' said John Young, president and chief executive
officer.
