<HEAD>London Stocks Hit New Post-Crash High</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New throughout.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks rose strongly in London on Wednesday,
propelled upward by better-than-expected U.S. trade figures.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 19.1
points, or 0.9 percent, to 2,155.8, its best close since the
October 1987 stock crash.
